<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910213-0095</DOCNO><DOCID>910213-0095.</DOCID><HL>   Union Texas Petroleum</HL><DATE>02/13/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   UTH</CO><IN>OIL, SECONDARY (OIS)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><LP>   HOUSTON -- Union Texas Petroleum Holdings Inc. said itsplanned 1991 capital spending budget of $377 million, isessentially flat from the $379 million the company estimatesit spent last year.   The energy concern said it plans to spend about $136million on the redevelopment of the U.K. North Sea PiperAlpha field and the development of a neighboring field, andabout $145 million for other overseas oil and gas interests.</LP><TEXT>   An explosion at the Piper Alpha field in 1989 destroyed aplatform and other assets valued at more than $1 billion andwiped out about 67% of the company's world-wide oil output.</TEXT></DOC>